-- IMG Worldwide Acquires Catalyst for Sports Consulting Business
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2013-01-08T06:34:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-08/img-worldwide-aquires-catalyst-for-sports-consulting-business.html
IMG Worldwide Inc., which manages
professional athletes such as quarterback  Peyton Manning , tennis
player Novak Djokovic and skier Lindsey Vonn, acquired Catalyst
Public Relations as part of its consulting business.  IMG Chairman and Chief Executive Mike Dolan said Catalyst
is a “perfect fit” and has a history of success in U.S.
professional sports as well as with global properties such as
the Olympics and soccer’s World Cup.  “This acquisition is part of an ongoing plan to further
expand our portfolio of key marketing services we can provide
our consulting clients around the world,” said George Pyne,
president of IMG’s Sports and Entertainment Group.  Financial terms of the agreement weren’t disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
